# Force binary handling for asset types so end-of-line conversion
# (core.autocrlf=true on Windows) can never corrupt them. Git's text/binary
# heuristic misfires on PDFs (mostly-ASCII streams), which would otherwise let
# a fresh Windows checkout insert CR bytes and break the file. Declared
# explicitly here; everything else keeps git's default autocrlf behaviour.
*.pdf   binary
*.docx  binary
*.xlsx  binary
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.gif   binary
*.ico   binary
*.ttf   binary
*.otf   binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.zip   binary
*.exe   binary
*.dll   binary
